    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it seems like you're saying most economists agree on this, but isn't there a huge debate about how these programs actually help people get back into the workforce? some experts argue that the safety net is a necessary floor that actually enables people to look for better jobs instead of just taking any low-wage work. why does that perspective seem less prominent in your analysis?",
